[00:01.080]--- Lesson 52  A pretty carpet 漂亮的地毯

[00:07.160]--- First listen and then answer the question.^听录音，然后回答以下问题。

[00:13.760]--- What is the writer's carpet made of?

[00:19.240]We have just moved into a new house and I have been working hard all morning.^我们刚刚搬进一所新房子，我辛辛苦苦地干了整整一个上午。

[00:27.600]I have been trying to get my new room in order.^我试图把我的新房间收拾整齐，

[00:32.040]This has not been easy because I own over a thousand books.^但这并不容易，因为我有1,000多本书。

[00:38.160]To make matters worse, the room is rather small, so I have temporarily put my books on the floor.^更糟糕的是房间还非常小，所以我暂时把书放在了地板上。

[00:47.160]At the moment, they cover every inch of floor space and I actually have to walk on them to get in or out of the room.^这会儿，书把地板的每一点空隙都占据了，我实际上是踩着这些书进出房间的。

[00:58.320]A short while ago, my sister helped me to carry one of my old bookcases up the stairs.^几分钟前，我妹妹帮我把一个旧书橱抬上了楼。

[01:06.880]She went into my room and got a big surprise when she saw all those books on the floor.^她走进我的房间，当她看到地板上的那些书时，大吃一惊。“

[01:14.800]'This is the prettiest carpet I have ever seen,' she said.^这是我见过的最漂亮的地毯，”她说。

[01:20.040]She gazed at it for some time then added,^她盯着“地毯”看了一会儿，又说：

[01:23.640]'You don't need bookcases at all. You can sit here in your spare time and read the carpet!'^“你根本用不着书橱，空闲时你可以坐在这儿读地毯！”

